cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with visual place recognition, which is a problem in computer vision. The paper specifically focuses on using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to extract features and localize discriminative visual landmarks for better place recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of CNNs for feature extraction and landmark localization could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experiments on open source datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
